panningModel

panningModel property

PanningModelType get panningModel

The panningModel property of the PannerNode is an enumerated value determining which spatialization algorithm to use to position the audio in 3D space.

The possible values are:

  • equalpower: Represents the equal-power panning algorithm, generally regarded as simple and efficient. equalpower is the default value.
  • HRTF: Renders a stereo output of higher quality than equalpower â€” it uses a convolution with measured impulse responses from human subjects.
